# ğŸš€ Kubernetes Local Setup on Windows (Step-by-Step)

This guide will help you install **Chocolatey**, **kubectl**, and **Minikube** on **Windows** and run Kubernetes locally.

---

## ğŸ§° Prerequisites

* Windows 10 / 11 (64-bit)
* Administrator access
* Virtualization enabled in BIOS

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ Install Chocolatey (Package Manager)

Chocolatey makes installing tools on Windows very easy.

### ğŸ”¹ Steps

1. Open **PowerShell as Administrator**
2. Run the following command:

```powershell
Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force; \
[System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = \
[System.Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol -bor 3072; \
iex ((New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://community.chocolatey.org/install.ps1'))
```

3. Close and reopen PowerShell

### ğŸ”¹ Verify Installation

```powershell
choco --version
```

You should see a version number.

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Install kubectl (Kubernetes CLI)

### ğŸ”¹ Install via Chocolatey

```powershell
choco install kubernetes-cli -y
```

### ğŸ”¹ Verify

```powershell
kubectl version --client
```

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Install Minikube

Minikube runs a local Kubernetes cluster.

### ğŸ”¹ Install

```powershell
choco install minikube -y
```

### ğŸ”¹ Verify

```powershell
minikube version
```

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Install Docker Desktop (Required)

Minikube needs a container runtime.

### ğŸ”¹ Download & Install

ğŸ‘‰ [https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/)

During install:

* Enable **WSL 2**
* Enable **Use WSL 2 backend**

Restart your system after installation.

### ğŸ”¹ Verify Docker

```powershell
docker version
```

You should see **Client and Server**.

---

## 5ï¸âƒ£ Start Minikube Cluster

### ğŸ”¹ Start Minikube using Docker driver

```powershell
minikube start --driver=docker
```

This may take a few minutes the first time.

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Verify Kubernetes Cluster

```powershell
kubectl get nodes
```

Expected output:

```
NAME       STATUS   ROLES           AGE   VERSION
minikube   Ready    control-plane   ...   ...
```

---

## 7ï¸âƒ£ Enable Ingress (Optional but Recommended)

```powershell
minikube addons enable ingress
```

Check:

```powershell
kubectl get pods -n ingress-nginx
```

---

## 8ï¸âƒ£ Useful Minikube Commands

```powershell
minikube status
minikube stop
minikube delete
minikube dashboard
```

---

## 9ï¸âƒ£ Common Issues & Fixes

### âŒ Virtualization Not Enabled

* Enable **Virtualization / SVM** in BIOS

### âŒ Docker not running

* Start Docker Desktop
* Wait until status = **Running**

### âŒ kubectl not recognized

* Restart PowerShell
* Check PATH

